title: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1882–83
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Notebook with marbled cover containing 161 samples with recipes for printing. Mostly brightly colored floral patterns.

Open: 33.7 x 40.6 x 8.9 cm (13 1/4 x 16 x 3 1/2 in.); Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts; 1945-55-11
